Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour two 9 inch pans. In a medium saucepan, heat butter, yogurt, chocolate and cola until chocolate is completely melted. In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, and baking soda. Add chocolate mixture, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Pour batter into two 9 inch round pans. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.